  "body": "In `RespondCollationBody()`. A proposer shouldn't have to sign again to reconstruct header to retrieve collation body for response. What it means is only the original proposer can respond with its collation body, and no one else can\r\n\r\n```go\r\nfunc RespondCollationBody(req p2p.Message, signer mainchain.Signer, collationFetcher sharding.CollationFetcher) (*messages.CollationBodyResponse, error) {\r\n\t...\r\n\tsig, err := signer.Sign(header.Hash())\r\n\t...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe correct work flow should be:\r\n1. proposer creates, signs and adds header to smc\r\n2. proposer broadcasts collation body to the rest of the network\r\n3. notary requests collation body to everyone in the network (not just the original proposer)\r\n4. anyone can respond notary back with the collation body\r\n\r\nHow we we can fix this;\r\n1. Store proposer signature to SMC by adding a signature field to CollationRecord\r\n2. Use collationBodyRequest's ChunkRoot to look up collationBody via BodyByChunkRoot. and we add BodyByChunkRoot method under interface collationFetcher\r\n\r\nWe can split this into two PRs, for 1 and 2",
